![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The `nth-child` selectors for the typing indicator dots appear to be incorrect given the HTML structure in `chatView.ts`. The parent `div` contains a `<span>` with text as its first child, followed by the three dot `<span>` elements. This means the dots are actually the 2nd, 3rd, and 4th children. The current selectors will result in a broken animation. To fix this, the selectors should be adjusted to target the correct child elements.

```suggestion
.typing-dot:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: -0.32s; }
.typing-dot:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: -0.16s; }
```

